{
  "name": "Judgement Cut",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Bukijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You take your weapon and coat it in your chakra, and use your raw skill to gauge the distance between yourself and your target.</p><p>Select a space you can see within range. All creatures within 5 feet of this space must succeed a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a target takes 5d8 Slashing damage on a failed save, or half as much on a success.</p><p>Additionally, you can choose to spend an additional 6 Chakra to use this jutsu again targeting the same space, forcing all creatures to repeat the saving throw. You can do this twice per casting.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above B-Rank increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the number of spaces you can select by +1. A creature can only be affected by one instance this jutsu at a time. </p>",
